# Content Enhancer Loop (Strict)

Follow this loop exactly for article enhancement tasks.

1. Create `temp_articles_checklist.txt` with one line per article and no extra text:
   - Format: `- [ ] <article-path>`
2. Pick the first unchecked article.
3. Improve only the article title to top-tier quality while preserving SEO keyword constraints.
4. Perform deep research on the title subject and write findings into a temp markdown file.
5. Translate the temp research content to Hebrew.
6. Replace article body content using the researched Hebrew content in the same article path.
7. Run local dev server and review the live article page output.
8. Remove unrelated links and fix formatting mismatches.
9. Mark the article as done in checklist:
   - Format: `- [x] <article-path>`
10. Continue until no unchecked lines remain.

Hard requirements:
- Preserve content schema fields and required frontmatter keys.
- Keep a single primary keyword and ensure it appears in the article H1.
- Keep internal links meaningful and relevant.
- Add explicit error logging for each loop step.
- Never modify unrelated files or unrelated schema fields.
